    Closed --> [*]

    note right of Unbound
        Created with no-arg constructor or SocketImpl constructor.
        bind() transitions to Bound.
        setPerformancePreferences() and setReceiveBufferSize()
        must be called before bind() to have full effect.
    end note

    note right of Bound
        bind() throws IOException if already bound.
        accept() blocks until a connection is made.
        setOption()/getOption() throw IOException if socket is closed.
    end note

    note right of Closed
        Terminal state. close() is idempotent.
        setOption()/getOption()/setReuseAddress() throw exceptions in Closed state.
        isBound() returns true if socket was bound prior to close.
    end note
